raw_meta_yaml:
{% set min_rust = "rust >=1.46" %}
{% set version = "0.26.2" %}
{% set build_number = 0 %}
{% set min_rust = "rust >=1.46" %}

package:
  name: oso
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/osohq/oso/archive/refs/tags/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0df339b5b5b3938360ed84b512eb1ad1af7e9288bcea32161417bb3770ab66cb

build:
  number: {{ build_number }}

requirements:
  build:
    - cffi                                   # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - make                                   # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - openssl                                # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - clangdev                               # [not osx and build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - {{ min_rust }}
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
  host:
    - make
    - clangdev  # [not osx]
    - openssl
    - python
    - pip
    - cffi >=1.0.0
  run:
    - python
    - cffi >=1.0.0

test:
  source_files:
    - languages/python/oso/tests
  imports:
    - oso
    - polar
  commands:
    - pip check
    - cd languages/python/oso
    - pytest -vv tests --cov=oso --cov=polar --no-cov-on-fail --cov-report=term-missing:skip-covered --cov-fail-under=84 -k "not test_parser_errors and not test_repr_when_logging"
  requires:
    - pip
    - pytest-cov
    - ruamel_yaml
    - sqlalchemy

about:
  home: https://github.com/osohq/oso
  summary: Oso is a batteries-included framework for building authorization in your application.
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  doc_url: https://docs.osohq.com
  dev_url: https://github.com/osohq/oso

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - alexpilot11
    - bollwyvl
